  "texts": [
    "You were far more likely to discover this bias via frequent granular-level estimation of local preferences, enabled by AI polling.",
    "While the AI pollster is not infallabale, and could conceivably give rise to errors of a similar magnitude as traditional polling, its ability to more frequently survey changes in public attitudes affords the Guildford voter an advantage in terms of probabilistic knowledge.",
    "This example clearly illustrates the path through which core voter knowledge, augmented by AI polling, can help voters better satisfy their preferences.",
    "However, the benefits of AI polling carry a systematic risk.",
    "The increased complexity of the methodology used to generate the frequent and granular estimates can be opaque, and hide potential biases in sampling and modeling."
